ranean region with benefits in discharge simulations also in well gauged areas.},
author = {Ciabatta, Luca and Brocca, Luca and Massari, Christian and Moramarco, Tommaso and Gabellani, Simone and Puca, Silvia and Wagner, Wolfgang},
doi = {10.1016/j.jag.2015.10.004},
file = {:home/nicolas/.local/share/data/Mendeley Ltd./Mendeley Desktop/Downloaded/Ciabatta et al. - 2016 - Rainfall-runoff modelling by using SM2RAIN-derived and state-of-the-art satellite rainfall products over Italy.pdf:pdf},
issn = {1872826X},
journal = {International Journal of Applied Earth Observation and Geoinformation},
keywords = {Floods,Hydrological modelling,Rainfall,Remote sensing,Soil moisture},
pages = {163--173},
publisher = {Elsevier B.V.},
title = {{Rainfall-runoff modelling by using SM2RAIN-derived and state-of-the-art satellite rainfall products over Italy}},
