and the consequent increase$\backslash$nin cold advection. Therefore, to the cast of the subtropical Andes both$\backslash$nhorizontal and vertical advection cool the lower troposphere, fostering$\backslash$nthe equatorward propagation of the cold front. To the west of the Andes,$\backslash$nhorizontal advection is largely offset by the strong warming associated$\backslash$nwith the enhanced subsidence over that region hindering the advance of$\backslash$nthe cold front into subtropical latitudes.},
